
Commando			Explanation

ls				list files and directories
ls -a				list all files and directories
mkdir name			make a directory called name
cd name				change to the directory called name
cd				change to home directory
cd ~				change to home directory
cd ..				change to parent directory
pwd				display the path of the current directory

cp file1 file2			copy file1 and call the copy file2
mv file1 file2			rename file1 to file2
mv file1 directory/file1	move file1 to specified directory
rm file				remove file
rmdir directory			remove directory
cat file			display a file
less file			display a file page by page
head file			show the first few lines of a file
tail file			show the last few lines of a file
grep keyword file		display occurences of keyword in a file
wc file				show the number of lines, words and characters of a file

command > file			redirect standard output to file
command >> file			append standard output to file
command < file			replace standard input with contents of file
command1 | command2		pipe standard output of command1 to command2
cat file1 file2 > file0		concatenate file1 and file2 to file0
sort				sort data by number and alphabetically
who				display currently logged in users

